Package es.usal.bicoverlapper.visualization.diagrams.overlapper

Class Summary
Cluster Abstract class for cluster representation.
ClusterSet ClusterSet keeps track of all the (bi)clusters returned by certain (bi)clustering algorithm, or any other organization of cluster as a group that would be necessary Each ClsuterSet has a representative color an label to distingish from other ClusterSets.
Edge Edge class connects two nodes by a directed edge.
ForcedNode Force directed nodes.
Graph A Graph is a set of Nodes, grouped in (overlapped) Clusters, that are classified in ResultSets.
Handle Deprecated.  
JProcessingPanel JProcessingPanel is a JComponent that emulates most of the Processing functions.
MaximalCluster Extension of Cluster, where each node is connected to any other in the Cluster (maximal graph or clique)
Node A node is an element that is subject to be in a group.
Overlapper This class visualizes biclusters as overlapping hulls on a force-directed graph layout.
RadialCluster RadialCluster class is an extension of Cluster, where an dummy node is added, called centerNode.
SpringEdge SpringEdge implements elastic edges.
